To avoid indiscriminate enhancement of all neurons (which would risk epilepsy), we restrict our intervention to excitatory L5 pyramidal neurons using the CaMKIIα promoter. Calcium/calmodulin-dependent protein kinase II alpha is expressed predominantly in forebrain excitatory neurons, with enrichment in cortical L5 and hippocampal CA1 pyramids (Mayford et al., 1996).

