11.1 Introduction: The Circadian Gating of Intelligence

Every biological computation occurs within a temporal envelope: the circadian rhythm. This 24-hour molecular clock, driven by the transcriptional-translational feedback loop of CLOCK, BMAL1, PER, and CRY, gates virtually every neural process relevant to the IISL (Takahashi, 2017). The circadian system controls:

