The expected value over horizon T is:

\mathbb{E}[I_{hybrid}] = (1 - p_{fail}) \cdot I_{augmented} + p_{fail} \cdot I_{degraded}

For p_{fail} even modestly above zero and T > \tau_{recovery}, the expected value falls below I_{CF} because the degraded state persists for a large fraction of the horizon.

