Proof. The control matrix \mathbf{G}(\mathbf{X}) has full row rank for all \mathbf{X} in the biologically admissible region, as the pillars provide independent actuation on each IISL variable (Pillars 1,2,3,6,7 affect B; Pillars 4,7 affect C; Pillars 5,6,8 affect E). By Chow's theorem, the system is controllable. The target \mathbf{X}_{HI} is within the positive orthant and satisfies the safety constraints established in Section 13.6, thus it is reachable. \square

